           SPELL=hostapd
         VERSION=1.0
          SOURCE=$SPELL-$VERSION.tar.gz
      SOURCE_GPG=gurus.gpg:$SOURCE.sig:WORKS_FOR_ME
SOURCE_DIRECTORY="$BUILD_DIRECTORY/$SPELL-$VERSION"
   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://hostap.epitest.fi/releases/$SOURCE
      LICENSE[0]=GPL
            DOCS="README*"
        WEB_SITE=http://hostap.epitest.fi/hostapd/
         ENTERED=20120705
           SHORT="IEEE 802.11 AP, IEEE 802.1X/WPA/WPA2/EAP/RADIUS Authenticator"
cat << EOF
hostapd is a user space daemon for access point and authentication servers.
It implements IEEE 802.11 access point management, IEEE 802.1X/WPA/WPA2/EAP
Authenticators, RADIUS client, EAP server, and RADIUS authentication server.

hostapd is designed to be a "daemon" program that runs in the background and acts
as the backend component controlling authentication. hostapd supports separate
frontend programs and an example text-based frontend, hostapd_cli, is included
with hostapd.
EOF
